parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to come undone during an accident, leading to increased risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle comes open upon impact
the seat belt comes out of the buckle
the rear seat belt buckle is inoperative
the rear seat belt cannot be pulled out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause pressure build-up in the fuel tank, leading to a fire, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel pump failure
pressure build-up in the fuel tank
vehicle catches on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, reduced performance, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant loss
white smoke from the exhaust
engine knocking or clunking sounds
engine stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A broken cam pulley can cause engine damage, reduced performance, and potentially leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling or failure to start
unusual engine noises
loss of power
engine warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden opening of the hood while driving can cause a loss of visibility, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The hood flies open while driving
obstructing the driver's view
and may cause damage to the hood
windshield
or other components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat mounting can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, it can also cause discomfort and distraction to the driver, compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: The driver's seat moves backwards or forwards unexpectedly
the seat feels unstable or loose
the seat mounting bolts are broken or damaged
the seat is difficult to adjust or maintain a fixed position.
